to:RuleAddition_FR_03 a owl:NamedIndividual,
        to:RuleAddition ;
    rdfs:label "FR Addition 3"@en ;
    to:additionNumber 3 ;
    to:appliedToLanguage to:French ;
    to:ruleText "UNRESOLVED: Nasal consonants at word-final position. Committee acknowledged ambiguity in mapping nasalized vowels [ɑ̃]/[ɔ̃] vs consonant-final nasals. Napoléon and champagne illustrate the pattern."@en .

